&quot;She is right you know, this is really not our fight, or our business, as much as it is the Furies.&quot;<br>
::Clotho nodded and spoke in her raspy voice.::<br>
&quot;This much is true sisters, Hecate has shown great injustice to the Priestes and Priestesses of the Titans. It was not like they were harming anyone, praying and following those who are not with us any longer. Does she not know a High Priest or Priestess is a vessel for the God or Goddess they were chosen for? Dear Alecto, how do you think Hecate would react if she came to find her Priestesses slaughtered and dead, and not just dead, but dead because there murderer was being a child who could not accept change?&quot;<br>
::She looked to the Furies.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hecategoddessofmagic>Hecate Goddess of Magic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/29/03 12:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=313.topic&index=78>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nefaria.com/gallery/1152x864/art/sorceress1152.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Forewarned</span><hr size=1> Iris came forward, her cheerful demeanor suddnely gone.<br>
<br>
::Dear Hecate, you tread on dangerous roads.  Do you know how many gods are upset with what you have done?  We three understand your fear in the uprising of the Titans, and also understand that something had to be done.  But the other gods do not see things as clearly as we do.  Even now, many of them plot against you.<br>
<br>
Hecate looked at the faces of her friends, and knew that what Iris said to be true.  She looked gloominly upon the floor, her shoulders slumping with fatigue.<br>
<br>
::I thank you for your warning.  I knew from the beginning that what I am doing may not be easy, but I did not know there would be so many opposition.  The Titans were never gods, they never worked towards building up their worshippers like the Olympians did.  All the Titans cared for was pleasing themselves, and terrorizing the mortals.  It was we Olympians that brought order into this world.  What I am doing is preventing the chaos that reigned in the past from coming again.  Surely even the most near-sighted Olympian must be able to see this.<br>
<br>
She looked at Iris, her dearest friend, and Iris came over and hugged her.<br>
<br>
::The priests and priestesses of the Titans were never following a god, they were following monsters. In fact the Titans are nothing more than the monsters which we gods occassionally slay.  The One-Eyed Cyclopes, Hecatonchires evil monsters with fifty heads and one-hundred arms each, and many others beyond count have roamed the earth, and we fought them, beat them, and imprisoned them.  Now they may be coming back.  Remember even our most holy father, Zeus, led the fight against them, and we all stood by him.  Zeus charged us with defending the world against these creatures, and that is what I am doing.  It seems many of our siblings have forgotten their duty, or is it that they have  decided to forsake their king?  But this fight has taken a toll on me and my priestesses.  I can't do this on my own anymore.  The fact that you three are here to tell me of this, must mean that you are on my side, right?<br>
<br>
The three looked at each other, and slowly nodded.  It appears that they weren't too happy about having to choose sides.<br>
<br>
::Thank you, I know how hard this must be on you all.  But I think my task now is to seek others as well.  Therefore I ask you three to return to your duties, and take no action yet.  Please be there for me when I seek your aid.  And I will see to things here.<br>
<br>
Hecate gave each of her friends a strong hug.  Without another word, the four of them blinked out, heading towards appointed roles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FFFF33>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23>The Olympian Gods</a> <font color=#FFFF33> - </font><a href="http://pub163.ezboard.com/bmythicalodysseyforum">Home</a><font color=#FFFF33> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.3m<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

